==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[bærlic|bærlīċ]]'' ‘barley-like’ (adjective), corresponding to ''[[bere]]'' + ''[[-ly]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈbɑ:li/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑː(r)li|-ɑː(r)li]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# A strong [[cereal]] of the genus ''Hordeum'', or its grains, often used as food or to make malted drinks.

